  "texts": [
    "Malicious actors can leverage backdoor attacks to gain access to LLMs or systems using a variety of methods (e.g., issuing API calls, malicious code auto-completions) [122].Attacker Techniques.",
    "To highlight privacy concerns, researchers have demonstrated a data-stealing attack by designing an injection that instructs the LLM to persuade the end user to divulge their real name [122].",
    "Below are some attack techniques that researchers have used to achieve this data-stealing attack:• Human-in-the-loop indirect prompting.",
    "Read operations (e.g., triggering a search query that then makes a request to the attacker, or retrieving URLs directly) are exploited to send information to the attacker [122].• Interacting in chat sessions.",
    "The model persuades a user to follow a URL into which the attacker inserts the user's name [122].• Invisible markdown image."
